   <Ritual>
      <Nerangs id="ritualNerangs">
         <ab>VytVrS82.14 (mss. 2005, 2007, 2010, 2030, 2040, 2101, 2104, 2106, 2109, 4000, 4010, 4020, 4050, 4055, 4161, 4162, 5020):</ab>
         <ab class="ab_indent">
            <em>aṣ̌aiia daδąmi aēsma baōiδi tauua āϑrō ahurahe mazdā̊ puϑra imąm aŋhuiiąmca aṣ̌aiiąmca raϑβąmca ratufritīmca</em> xšnūman ān ī bēd dō bār guftan agar ahlawān bēd  
            <em>auuaŋ́hā̊ frauuaṣ̌aiiō</em> bē gōwišn tā <em>yasnąsca vaɱąsca</em>.</ab> 
         <ab class="ab_indent">
            "At <em>aṣ̌aiia daδąmi aēsma baōiδi tauua āϑrō ahurahe mazdā̊ puϑra imąm aŋhuiiąmca aṣ̌aiiąmca raϑβąmca ratufritīmca</em>, they shoud recite twice the corresponding <em>šnūman</em>. 
            If it is (a liturgy) for the <em>ahlawān</em>, they have to recite <em>auuaŋ́hā̊ frauuaṣ̌aiiō</em> until <em>yasnąsca vaɱąsca</em>."</ab>
      </Nerangs>
   </Ritual>
